verses.text: The king’s heart \add is\add* in the hand of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, \add as\add* the rivers of water : he turneth it whithersoever he will.
Every way of a man \add is\add* right in his own eyes : but the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* pondereth the hearts.
To do justice and judgment \add is\add* more acceptable to the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* than sacrifice.
An high look , and a proud heart , \add and\add* the plowing of the wicked , \add is\add* sin.\f + \fr 21.4 \ft An…: Heb. Haughtiness of eyes\f*\f + \fr 21.4 \ft the plowing: or, the light\f*
The thoughts of the diligent \add tend\add* only to plenteousness ; but of every one \add that is\add* hasty only to want.
The getting of treasures by a lying tongue \add is\add* a vanity tossed to and fro of them that seek death.
The robbery of the wicked shall destroy them; because they refuse to do judgment.\f + \fr 21.7 \ft destroy…: Heb. saw them, or, dwell with them\f*
The way of man \add is\add* froward and strange : but \add as for\add* the pure , his work \add is\add* right.

\add It is\add* better to dwell in a corner of the housetop , than with a brawling woman in a wide house.\f + \fr 21.9 \ft a brawling…: Heb. a woman of contentions\f*\f + \fr 21.9 \ft a wide…: Heb. an house of society\f*
The soul of the wicked desireth evil : his neighbour findeth no favour in his eyes.\f + \fr 21.10 \ft findeth…: Heb. is not favoured\f*
When the scorner is punished , the simple is made wise : and when the wise is instructed , he receiveth knowledge.
The righteous \add man\add* wisely considereth the house of the wicked : \add but God\add* overthroweth the wicked for \add their\add* wickedness.
Whoso stoppeth his ears at the cry of the poor , he also shall cry himself, but shall not be heard.
A gift in secret pacifieth anger : and a reward in the bosom strong wrath.
\add It is\add* joy to the just to do judgment : but destruction \add shall be\add* to the workers of iniquity.
The man that wandereth out of the way of understanding shall remain in the congregation of the dead.
He that loveth pleasure \add shall be\add* a poor man : he that loveth wine and oil shall not be rich.\f + \fr 21.17 \ft pleasure: or, sport\f*
The wicked \add shall be\add* a ransom for the righteous , and the transgressor for the upright.
\add It is\add* better to dwell in the wilderness , than with a contentious and an angry woman.\f + \fr 21.19 \ft in…: Heb. in the land of the desert\f*
\add There is\add* treasure to be desired and oil in the dwelling of the wise ; but a foolish man spendeth it up.
He that followeth after righteousness and mercy findeth life , righteousness , and honour.
A wise \add man\add* scaleth the city of the mighty , and casteth down the strength of the confidence thereof.
Whoso keepeth his mouth and his tongue keepeth his soul from troubles.
Proud \add and\add* haughty scorner \add is\add* his name , who dealeth in proud wrath.\f + \fr 21.24 \ft in proud…: Heb. in the wrath of pride\f* \p
The desire of the slothful killeth him; for his hands refuse to labour.
He coveteth greedily all the day long: but the righteous giveth and spareth not.
The sacrifice of the wicked \add is\add* abomination : how much more, \add when\add* he bringeth it with a wicked mind ?\f + \fr 21.27 \ft with…: Heb. in wickedness?\f*
A false witness shall perish : but the man that heareth speaketh constantly.\f + \fr 21.28 \ft A…: Heb. A witness of lies\f*
A wicked man hardeneth his face : but \add as for\add* the upright , he directeth his way.\f + \fr 21.29 \ft directeth: or, considereth\f* \p
\add There is\add* no wisdom nor understanding nor counsel against the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
The horse \add is\add* prepared against the day of battle : but safety \add is\add* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 21.31 \ft safety: or, victory\f*
